tracks.subject: Request for information about accessible travel - general query, no routes requested
tracks.description: Dublin based Cx requested general information about accessible travel with wheelchair. Explained Free Travel Pass, travel on Dub Bus - all accessible but not guaranteed, driver can lower ramp and request that the wheelchair area be vacated (if occupied by a stroller) but cannot make someone move. IR booking process (through CCC and online) explained about wheelchair spaces on trains, travel assistance (inc ramps) noting best to request more than 24 hours. Noted all LUAS stations accessible with ramps at each end of platform. Explained DART hubs inc how to request assistance at unstaffed station. Explained that all Bus Eir intercity routes are accessible and most rural but access should be requested at least 24 hours ahead to ensure that an accessible bus is allocated to their route. Recommended TFI Live for most current info on accessible services & stations etc as well as on any route disruptions.
